  This code is problematic because it uses varargs in the constructor signature but does not pass any arguments to the constructor when creating an instance of the class. As a result, the constructor will throw a `MissingFormatArgumentException` at runtime.

To fix this issue, you can either pass some dummy values as arguments to the constructor or remove the varargs parameter altogether. Here's an example of how you could modify the code to fix the issue:
```
public class RefactorWithVarArgsBug {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		RefactorWithVarArgsBug o = new RefactorWithVarArgsBug();
	}

	public RefactorWithVarArgsBug() {

	}
}
```
In this example, we've removed the varargs parameter from the constructor and instead passed an empty argument list to the `new` operator. This will allow the code to compile and run without any issues.

