```
public class Rectangle {
    private double height;

    /**
     * Sets the dimension of the rectangle based on the given name and value.
     * @param name The name of the dimension (e.g. "height")
     * @param value The value of the dimension
     */
    public void setDimension(String name, double value) {
        if (name.equals("height")) {
            this.height = value;
        } 
    }
}
```
This comment explains what the method does and provides an example of how it can be used. It also includes a brief description of the purpose of the method, which is to set the dimension of the rectangle based on the given name and value.

